        Official Singles Chart on 10/12/2021

        10 December 2021 - 16 December 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Nope, the 3 song rule is only 3 per artist across EVERY album, not 3 songs per album.

        Otherwise, we would’ve seen a lot more Adele songs recently, as a lot of them were high on streaming when Easy On Me was announced/released.

        Also, with songs with two lead artists, OCC credits the first one listed as the main artist, which is why it counts for Ed Sheeran (Ed Sheeran with Elton John) and not for Justin Bieber (The Kid LAROI with Justin Bieber).
